column2: Question
Do you think things in this country are generally going in the right direction or have gotten pretty seriously off on the wrong track?

If the 2016 presidential election were being held today and the candidates were Hillary Clinton and Tim Kaine, the Democrats and Donald Trump and Mike Pence, the Republicans for whom would you vote/lean toward?
For Clinton supporters, would that be more a vote for Hillary Clinton or more a vote against Donald Trump?
For Trump supporters, would that be more a vote for Donald Trump or more a vote against Hillary Clinton?

If the 2016 presidential election were being held today and the candidates were Hillary Clinton and Tim Kaine, the Democrats, Donald Trump and Mike Pence, the Republicans, Gary Johnson and Bill Weld of the Libertarian Party and Jill Stein and Ajamu Baraka of the Green party, for whom would you vote/lean toward?
For Clinton supporters, how important is it that your candidate has the best positions on the issues?
For Trump supporters, how important is it that your candidate has the best positions on the issues?
For Clinton supporters, how important is it that your candidate is the strongest leader?
For Trump supporters, how important is it that your candidate is the strongest leader?
For Clinton supporters, how important is it that your candidate is most qualified to be president?
For Trump supporters, how important is it that your candidate is most qualified to be president?
For Clinton supporters, how much is it a factor that you oppose the other candidate?
For Trump supporters, how much is it a factor that you oppose the other candidate?
For Clinton supporters, how important is it that voting for your candidate sends a message to the political establishment?
For Trump supporters, how important is it that voting for your candidate sends a message to the political establishment?
For Clinton supporters, how important is it that your candidate is more honest and trustworthy?
For Trump supporters, how important is it that your candidate is more honest and trustworthy?

Would you like the next president to be someone who puts an especially major focus on trying to improve race relations in this country or someone who  does not put an especially major focus on this issue?

column3: Does not try to improve race relations

column2: Would you like the next president to be someone who supports trade agreements between the United States and other countries or someone who opposes them?
Would you like the next president to be someone who supports the international trade agreement known as the Trans-Pacific Partnership, or someone who  opposes this agreement?

Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Donald Trump?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Mike Pence?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Barack Obama?

Which vision of America is closer to your own: America is in decline and the issues facing our country today threaten our way of life and demand a president who will establish law and order or America is the greatest nation on earth and is stronger when all citizens are valued and work together to solve our toughest problems?
If the 2016 Senate election in Georgia were being held today and the candidates were Jim Barksdale, the Democrat and Johnny Isakson, the Republican, for whom would you vote/lean toward?

Do you have more confidence in Hillary Clinton or Donald Trump to deal with foreign affairs?
Do you have more confidence in Hillary Clinton or Donald Trump to deal with terrorism?
